biz.onomato.frskydash

Class FrSkyServer

  • java.lang.Object
    • Service
      • biz.onomato.frskydash.FrSkyServer

  • public class FrSkyServer
extends Service
    Main server service. This service will get started by the first Activity launched. It will stay alive even if the application is "minimized". It will only be closed by a press on the "Back" button while on the Dashboard.

    Serves as a store for Models, Channels and Alarms

    Receives bytebuffer from BluetoothSerialService, and parses this into individual Frames that is then sent to the respective Channel, Alarm or Hub. The frame is also sent to the DataLogger for logging to file.

    Activities should bind to this service using startService and bindService

    Communication from Service to Activities: Send broadcasts
    FIXME: Cleanup Activity -> Service
    Communication from Activity to Service: Method call, startservice with intent, or broadcast
    Author:
    eso

      • _sourceChannelMap

        private static java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.Integer,Channel> _sourceChannelMap

        A collection of Channel objects as sources. These Channels are available technical Channels used as source. This means it matches a certain type of sensor, analog value or rssi value. These are not registered for listening. Only the Channels the user creates are registered for listening.

        The Channels created by a user are stored on the Model instance and hold a certain configuration for these source channels.

        Example: If a user for instance wants the Analog port 1 to be displayed as a voltage divided by 3 (1 cell for a 3 cell lipo being connected) he can configure this Channel with the divider and then it will be registered listening and displaying the adapted value. The same source channel (for Analog port 1) can then also be configured as an actual channel on the model without divider showing the complete lipo pack voltage.
